      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MINTER MULWEE (1) was prominent early from the tricky draw and did a fair job to be beaten 4 lengths into third (23.35) at this track in a Grade 5 over 400m. Winning claims. MERGER (2) turned in a plain run last time when sixth at this track over 400m behind Theo The Great (23.58) in a Grade 5. Should be about the money. DANIEL KEEPING (7) put in a much better performance last start when in the placings at this track behind Rattlin' Bye (23.32) in a Grade 5. Stalked the pace but found the line strongly. Form from his last run is proving to be solid. Leading chance. ZIPPING DALY (4) cannot be left out after placing here at this trip last start.",
